  <h2>When to Call a Professional vs. When to Wait</h2>

  <p>If you're experiencing signs 1, 3, or 5 — smoke in the room, very sluggish draw, or visible nest/debris — don't use the fireplace until it's been professionally cleaned. These are active safety issues, not things to monitor through another season.</p>

  <p>If you're experiencing signs 2 or 4 — smell or visible soot — it's time to book a clean, but you're not in immediate danger from a single fire. Don't leave it until winter though; book in April or May before the pre-winter rush fills up available appointments.</p>

  <p>Signs 6 and 7 — overdue clean or unknown history — are about prevention. A professional clean is straightforward, takes less than an hour and a half, and costs significantly less than dealing with the consequences of a chimney fire or failed insurance claim.</p>
